message:
More than 5 copilot_live_turn_failed events in 15 minutes for ${CUSTOMER_LABEL}.

The canned fallback should be hiding most of these from end users, but persistent failures point at: Anthropic outage / quota, Apex REST callout failure (memory persistence), or a bug in the orchestrator that hits every turn.

First step: open one log row, read the @error field, and check whether @source is 'canned' downstream. If yes, customer is degraded but not down. If a 5xx is reaching the user, escalate.

Runbook: docs/runbook.md §10–11.

@oncall-${CUSTOMER_LABEL}
